cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper discusses mobility management and performance monitoring in heterogeneous wireless networks, which are topics related to computer networks and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses mechanisms for connectivity check and performance monitoring, which are related to security and cryptography (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of batteries in Mobile Hosts, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and scalability of monitoring thousands of flows, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
